Text.SourceString: Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>? As in <PlayerName>$player</> <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>It’s nice to finally meet you!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>? As in <PlayerName>$player</> <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>It’s nice to finally meet you!

Text.SourceString: Farmer? Cool.//I’m one of the doctors here.
Text.LocalizedString: Farmer? Cool.//I’m one of the doctors here.

Text.SourceString: I’m starting to worry about that recycling center near the park.//Should I stop taking stuff there?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m starting to worry about that recycling center near the park.//Should I stop taking stuff there?

Text.SourceString: I don’t know if you’ve noticed, but it looks like it’s overflowing.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know if you’ve noticed, but it looks like it’s overflowing.

Text.SourceString: There are empty sites here we can repurpose.
Text.LocalizedString: There are empty sites here we can repurpose.

Text.SourceString: Mr. Mayor thought a community garden would make a great space for outdoor activities.//As a doctor, I agree it’s a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It’ll give people another reason to move their bodies.
Text.LocalizedString: Mr. Mayor thought a community garden would make a great space for outdoor activities.//As a doctor, I agree it’s a great idea.//<portrait=happy>It’ll give people another reason to move their bodies.

Text.SourceString: I can see how facilities like a recycling center or a community garden could be good for us.//<portrait=annoyed>But I don’t know about upgrading other buildings.
Text.LocalizedString: I can see how facilities like a recycling center or a community garden could be good for us.//<portrait=annoyed>But I don’t know about upgrading other buildings.

Text.SourceString: I like how some of the buildings here are old. Like the mansion or the lighthouse.//They feel like a time capsule, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I like how some of the buildings here are old. Like the mansion or the lighthouse.//They feel like a time capsule, you know?

Text.SourceString: I average around fourish hours a day at work…//I usually work from 10 am to 2 pm, seeing patients, reviewing medical histories, or doing inventory.//<NPCName>Charles</> runs the reception most of the time.
Text.LocalizedString: I average around fourish hours a day at work…//I usually work from 10 am to 2 pm, seeing patients, reviewing medical histories, or doing inventory.//<NPCName>Charles</> runs the reception most of the time.

Text.SourceString: If I had to choose…//My favorite part of the job is creating care plans with patients.
Text.LocalizedString: If I had to choose…//My favorite part of the job is creating care plans with patients.

Text.SourceString: I’m used to high-stress situations.//I feel like that’s when my knowledge and training really kick in.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m used to high-stress situations.//I feel like that’s when my knowledge and training really kick in.

Text.SourceString: It sounds horrible, but the adrenaline rush is addictive.
Text.LocalizedString: It sounds horrible, but the adrenaline rush is addictive.

Text.SourceString: Paying attention to what you eat is a great way to stay healthy in the long run.//Prevention is worth more than any cure.
Text.LocalizedString: Paying attention to what you eat is a great way to stay healthy in the long run.//Prevention is worth more than any cure.

Text.SourceString: Make sure to include fresh vegetables in your diet.//They’re a great source of fiber and nutrients.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to include fresh vegetables in your diet.//They’re a great source of fiber and nutrients.

Text.SourceString: It would also make my job a whole lot easier! Heh, heh.
Text.LocalizedString: It would also make my job a whole lot easier! Heh, heh.

Text.SourceString: I get all my groceries at <NPCName>Sam's</>.//I love how he buys from local sources.
Text.LocalizedString: I get all my groceries at <NPCName>Sam's</>.//I love how he buys from local sources.

Text.SourceString: The bad thing about <NPCName>Sam's</> is you can’t really find off-season items.
Text.LocalizedString: The bad thing about <NPCName>Sam's</> is you can’t really find off-season items.

Text.SourceString: Just holler whenever you have questions about medicine or health.//I know people get nervous about little things like moles or rashes sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Just holler whenever you have questions about medicine or health.//I know people get nervous about little things like moles or rashes sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Let me help by giving you peace of mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me help by giving you peace of mind.

Text.SourceString: Being in the sun is fine as long as you remember to wear sunscreen.
Text.LocalizedString: Being in the sun is fine as long as you remember to wear sunscreen.

Text.SourceString: Oh, another thing!//<portrait=normal>Remember to reapply sunscreen every few hours. That part’s important, and people always forget.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, another thing!//<portrait=normal>Remember to reapply sunscreen every few hours. That part’s important, and people always forget.

Text.SourceString: Playing pool after work is a great way to make new friends.//<portrait=normal>But to be frank, I do it mostly because I think I’m pretty good at it.//<portrait=happy>It feels good to win, heh, heh.
Text.LocalizedString: Playing pool after work is a great way to make new friends.//<portrait=normal>But to be frank, I do it mostly because I think I’m pretty good at it.//<portrait=happy>It feels good to win, heh, heh.

Text.SourceString: I should wear regular clothes more.//<portrait=normal>I’m too lazy to change after my shift, so I just go around in scrubs.
Text.LocalizedString: I should wear regular clothes more.//<portrait=normal>I’m too lazy to change after my shift, so I just go around in scrubs.

Text.SourceString: I notice people here love fishing.//I’m all for it, because I think it’s important to unwind.
Text.LocalizedString: I notice people here love fishing.//I’m all for it, because I think it’s important to unwind.

Text.SourceString: Yeah! Fishing totally teaches patience.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah! Fishing totally teaches patience.

Text.SourceString: Chess is all about planning and strategy, just like health.//Well, for me, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: Chess is all about planning and strategy, just like health.//Well, for me, anyway.

Text.SourceString: Heh, heh… You got me!//<portrait=normal>I do always find a way to bring the conversation back to health talk.
Text.LocalizedString: Heh, heh… You got me!//<portrait=normal>I do always find a way to bring the conversation back to health talk.

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually work on Fridays unless I have an appointment.//Or if there’s an emergency or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually work on Fridays unless I have an appointment.//Or if there’s an emergency or something.

Text.SourceString: I’m not too worried about it. The clinic’s usually very quiet.//<NPCName>Charles</> will do just fine on his own.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not too worried about it. The clinic’s usually very quiet.//<NPCName>Charles</> will do just fine on his own.

Text.SourceString: How’s your week been so far?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your week been so far?

Text.SourceString: I think I might need to go to <NPCName>Sam's</> tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I might need to go to <NPCName>Sam's</> tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: We sell medicines and vitamins at the clinic.//They can quickly restore your health, so keep some in your backpack just in case.
Text.LocalizedString: We sell medicines and vitamins at the clinic.//They can quickly restore your health, so keep some in your backpack just in case.

Text.SourceString: Useful for an active person like you, no?
Text.LocalizedString: Useful for an active person like you, no?

Text.SourceString: I’m not a very good cook, but I try to eat homemade food when I can.//It’s better for you.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a very good cook, but I try to eat homemade food when I can.//It’s better for you.

Text.SourceString: I still eat out quite a bit, though! Heh, heh… Old habits die hard, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I still eat out quite a bit, though! Heh, heh… Old habits die hard, huh?

Text.SourceString: My tattoos?//<portrait=normal>I got most of them at places I was dispatched to. My experiences in the universal doctor program will stay with me forever.//They’re part of me, just like these tattoos.
Text.LocalizedString: My tattoos?//<portrait=normal>I got most of them at places I was dispatched to. My experiences in the universal doctor program will stay with me forever.//They’re part of me, just like these tattoos.

Text.SourceString: Ready for Monday, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Ready for Monday, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Make sure to drink enough water, okay?//Our bodies need it.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to drink enough water, okay?//Our bodies need it.

Text.SourceString: It’s so easy to get carried away and forget to listen to our bodies.//I’m guilty of that too.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so easy to get carried away and forget to listen to our bodies.//I’m guilty of that too.

Text.SourceString: Ugh… Fashion is hard.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh… Fashion is hard.

Text.SourceString: I tried “fashion,” or whatever, back in med school.//Let’s just say I’m glad social media wasn’t big back then.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried “fashion,” or whatever, back in med school.//Let’s just say I’m glad social media wasn’t big back then.

Text.SourceString: I don’t need any reminders of my med school days.//Though I do have some old pictures in a box somewhere.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll show you someday.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t need any reminders of my med school days.//Though I do have some old pictures in a box somewhere.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll show you someday.

Text.SourceString: Who knows…
Text.LocalizedString: Who knows…

Text.SourceString: One of the things I find most challenging about being a doctor is sometimes patients lie.//<portrait=normal>While it’s harmless in most cases, it’s always best to be honest with your doctor.
Text.LocalizedString: One of the things I find most challenging about being a doctor is sometimes patients lie.//<portrait=normal>While it’s harmless in most cases, it’s always best to be honest with your doctor.

Text.SourceString: It’s important for doctors to know your complete medical history to give you the best care possible.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s important for doctors to know your complete medical history to give you the best care possible.

Text.SourceString: I should totally rock a coat like <NPCName>Charles</> does.//<portrait=normal>Look at him, all sleek and stylish. That coat just adds a certain oomph, doesn't it?
Text.LocalizedString: I should totally rock a coat like <NPCName>Charles</> does.//<portrait=normal>Look at him, all sleek and stylish. That coat just adds a certain oomph, doesn't it?

Text.SourceString: But it’s just so hot and restricting.//And seriously, can't run a decent sprint with that coat flapping around like crazy.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s just so hot and restricting.//And seriously, can't run a decent sprint with that coat flapping around like crazy.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, I'm so used to scrubs. Anything else feels weird and constricting, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, I'm so used to scrubs. Anything else feels weird and constricting, you know?

Text.SourceString: Can you tell I dig green?//<portrait=happy>Ha! It's like my signature color.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you tell I dig green?//<portrait=happy>Ha! It's like my signature color.

Text.SourceString: I'm all about that simple life. As long as I've got a hot meal on the table, I consider it a good day.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm all about that simple life. As long as I've got a hot meal on the table, I consider it a good day.

Text.SourceString: Volleyball isn't exactly my forte yet, but hey, I won't turn down a game if someone asks.//Gotta keep the ball rolling!
Text.LocalizedString: Volleyball isn't exactly my forte yet, but hey, I won't turn down a game if someone asks.//Gotta keep the ball rolling!

Text.SourceString: Back in the day, I was part of this universal doctor program, traveling all over the world to help out.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in the day, I was part of this universal doctor program, traveling all over the world to help out.

Text.SourceString: The pay wasn’t good, but you get one heck of a lot of experience. Plus the satisfaction of helping people in need.
Text.LocalizedString: The pay wasn’t good, but you get one heck of a lot of experience. Plus the satisfaction of helping people in need.

Text.SourceString: Oh, and let me tell you, foreign travel really opens up your mind and toughens you up.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, and let me tell you, foreign travel really opens up your mind and toughens you up.

Text.SourceString: As a farmer, you must get a lot of daily exercise, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: As a farmer, you must get a lot of daily exercise, yeah?

Text.SourceString: A pet? Hmm… <NPCName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out of hiding when she’s home.//<portrait=annoyed>Does that count?
Text.LocalizedString: A pet? Hmm… <NPCName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out of hiding when she’s home.//<portrait=annoyed>Does that count?

Text.SourceString: I’m not sure if it’s male or female. All I know is she calls the lizard Tin.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not sure if it’s male or female. All I know is she calls the lizard Tin.

Text.SourceString: I try my best to live a healthy life, but some days it's harder than others, you know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: I try my best to live a healthy life, but some days it's harder than others, you know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: Today's plan is to just chill out and take it easy.//How about you?
Text.LocalizedString: Today's plan is to just chill out and take it easy.//How about you?

Text.SourceString: Do you like to hang out at the Local Tavern, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The live music on the weekends is where it's at.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you like to hang out at the Local Tavern, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The live music on the weekends is where it's at.

Text.SourceString: That <NPCName>Theo</> is really something, isn’t he?//That guy's got serious talent.
Text.LocalizedString: That <NPCName>Theo</> is really something, isn’t he?//That guy's got serious talent.

Text.SourceString: It’s not easy for me to find someone I want to spend my life with.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not easy for me to find someone I want to spend my life with.

Text.SourceString: Guess I've always been too busy to really think about settling down and starting a family.//But truth be told, long-term commitment scares me.
Text.LocalizedString: Guess I've always been too busy to really think about settling down and starting a family.//But truth be told, long-term commitment scares me.

Text.SourceString: Well, lucky for me, I don't have work tomorrow. But you seem to be on the grind every single day, am I right?
Text.LocalizedString: Well, lucky for me, I don't have work tomorrow. But you seem to be on the grind every single day, am I right?

Text.SourceString: If you need anything from the clinic, <NPCName>Charles</> should be in.
Text.LocalizedString: If you need anything from the clinic, <NPCName>Charles</> should be in.

Text.SourceString: Maybe, just maybe, tomorrow will be the day I finally go grocery shopping.//Who knows, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe, just maybe, tomorrow will be the day I finally go grocery shopping.//Who knows, right?

Text.SourceString: But hey, don't hold your breath on that one.
Text.LocalizedString: But hey, don't hold your breath on that one.

Text.SourceString: Not all my tattoos have some deep, profound meaning behind them.
Text.LocalizedString: Not all my tattoos have some deep, profound meaning behind them.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes you just gotta go with the flow, trust your instincts, and get inked.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes you just gotta go with the flow, trust your instincts, and get inked.

Text.SourceString: My hair has been rocking the green look for so long, I wouldn't even know how to answer if you asked about my natural hair color.
Text.LocalizedString: My hair has been rocking the green look for so long, I wouldn't even know how to answer if you asked about my natural hair color.

Text.SourceString: Wait, hold up! You've seen me where exactly?!
Text.LocalizedString: Wait, hold up! You've seen me where exactly?!

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to scare you, but I don’t think that was me.//I don’t go to the forest.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to scare you, but I don’t think that was me.//I don’t go to the forest.

Text.SourceString: Here’s a nonmedical tip for you. Eat your food in one sitting so it doesn’t go stale.
Text.LocalizedString: Here’s a nonmedical tip for you. Eat your food in one sitting so it doesn’t go stale.

Text.SourceString: Funny thing is, the food around here doesn't seem to spoil.//It's like magic or something.
Text.LocalizedString: Funny thing is, the food around here doesn't seem to spoil.//It's like magic or something.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Charles</> has to take his antihistamine…//I don’t know what else to tell him. It will literally make him feel better.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Charles</> has to take his antihistamine…//I don’t know what else to tell him. It will literally make him feel better.

Text.SourceString: Gotta say, not really a big fan of Spring. It’s just not for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta say, not really a big fan of Spring. It’s just not for me.

Text.SourceString: We do our restocking every Spring… Makes it easier to remember.//Spring…restocking. See?
Text.LocalizedString: We do our restocking every Spring… Makes it easier to remember.//Spring…restocking. See?

Text.SourceString: Have you had your flu vaccine yet?//I recommend getting it every year. Even if the strain changes, at least you'll have some protection.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you had your flu vaccine yet?//I recommend getting it every year. Even if the strain changes, at least you'll have some protection.

Text.SourceString: Most people usually get their flu vaccines in Winter or Spring. That’s when you’re most vulnerable.//I get mine in Fall to prepare for the coming season. Give it a try, see how it feels.
Text.LocalizedString: Most people usually get their flu vaccines in Winter or Spring. That’s when you’re most vulnerable.//I get mine in Fall to prepare for the coming season. Give it a try, see how it feels.

Text.SourceString: The Cherry Blossom Festival was really nice, wasn’t it?//<portrait=normal>I had a lot of fun.
Text.LocalizedString: The Cherry Blossom Festival was really nice, wasn’t it?//<portrait=normal>I had a lot of fun.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about <NPCName>Charles</>. He’s in good hands.//<portrait=normal>I've got everything under control. Let me do the worrying for the both of us, cool?
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about <NPCName>Charles</>. He’s in good hands.//<portrait=normal>I've got everything under control. Let me do the worrying for the both of us, cool?

Text.SourceString: Phew, are you sweating as much as I am? This heat is intense!
Text.LocalizedString: Phew, are you sweating as much as I am? This heat is intense!

Text.SourceString: It’s so hot, <PlayerName>$player</>.//It takes me back to my days volunteering in the doctor program.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so hot, <PlayerName>$player</>.//It takes me back to my days volunteering in the doctor program.

Text.SourceString: Good thing I'm not wearing a full-blown doctor's coat in this heat. Loose clothing all the way.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing I'm not wearing a full-blown doctor's coat in this heat. Loose clothing all the way.

Text.SourceString: Gotta give your body room to breathe… Not sandals, though.//<portrait=happy>I can’t run in those.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta give your body room to breathe… Not sandals, though.//<portrait=happy>I can’t run in those.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Charles</> and I always prepare for medical emergencies at the Beach Cleanup Festival… Nothing in particular.//It’s good to have doctors around at big gatherings in case someone gets heatstroke or something like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Charles</> and I always prepare for medical emergencies at the Beach Cleanup Festival… Nothing in particular.//It’s good to have doctors around at big gatherings in case someone gets heatstroke or something like that.

Text.SourceString: Will you be entering the swimming contest?
Text.LocalizedString: Will you be entering the swimming contest?

Text.SourceString: I think <NPCName>Sunny</> is going to win. He’s got some stamina… Very fast swimmer.
Text.LocalizedString: I think <NPCName>Sunny</> is going to win. He’s got some stamina… Very fast swimmer.

Text.SourceString: I got this small handheld fan… Oh, so good.//<portrait=normal>Fully automated, battery operated, and all that. You can take it with you in your pocket. The perfect Summer toy.
Text.LocalizedString: I got this small handheld fan… Oh, so good.//<portrait=normal>Fully automated, battery operated, and all that. You can take it with you in your pocket. The perfect Summer toy.

Text.SourceString: I had one, anyway… I don’t have the fan anymore.//Accidentally stepped on it. And nobody sells them here.
Text.LocalizedString: I had one, anyway… I don’t have the fan anymore.//Accidentally stepped on it. And nobody sells them here.

Text.SourceString: We have so many melons at home. I think <NpcName>Millie</> might have gone a little overboard…
Text.LocalizedString: We have so many melons at home. I think <NpcName>Millie</> might have gone a little overboard…

Text.SourceString: Finally, the perfect weather for eating curry.//Curry in Summer is fine, of course, but the heat from inside and out can be too much sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, the perfect weather for eating curry.//Curry in Summer is fine, of course, but the heat from inside and out can be too much sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I'm so glad the air has cooled down. It's a breath of fresh air, quite literally.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm so glad the air has cooled down. It's a breath of fresh air, quite literally.

Text.SourceString: What is it they say about Fall? Sweater weather?//<portrait=normal>Yeah, I think that’s right.
Text.LocalizedString: What is it they say about Fall? Sweater weather?//<portrait=normal>Yeah, I think that’s right.

Text.SourceString: I’ve heard only certain animals come out in Fall, but I’m no animal expert.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Millie</> probably knows way more than I do. She's got all the facts.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve heard only certain animals come out in Fall, but I’m no animal expert.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Millie</> probably knows way more than I do. She's got all the facts.

Text.SourceString: Are you going to show your crops at the Harvest Festival?//<portrait=happy>I love seeing everyone’s hard work.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to show your crops at the Harvest Festival?//<portrait=happy>I love seeing everyone’s hard work.

Text.SourceString: I think tonight's dinner is gonna be curry. Seems like the right weather for it.
Text.LocalizedString: I think tonight's dinner is gonna be curry. Seems like the right weather for it.

Text.SourceString: When I was traveling around the world, most of the places I was dispatched to were really hot.//<portrait=happy>I gotta say, it's a breath of fresh air to finally settle somewhere with a proper Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was traveling around the world, most of the places I was dispatched to were really hot.//<portrait=happy>I gotta say, it's a breath of fresh air to finally settle somewhere with a proper Winter.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever think about how lucky we are to have Winter?//I'd take layering up in the cold over constantly sweating in the heat any day.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever think about how lucky we are to have Winter?//I'd take layering up in the cold over constantly sweating in the heat any day.

Text.SourceString: Winter is usually our busiest season. People tend to get sick more often, which is why I prefer getting my flu shot in Fall.//It's all about preparation, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is usually our busiest season. People tend to get sick more often, which is why I prefer getting my flu shot in Fall.//It's all about preparation, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: We've stocked up on plenty of cold medicine for this season.//The weather is dry and cold, just the way those viruses like it.
Text.LocalizedString: We've stocked up on plenty of cold medicine for this season.//The weather is dry and cold, just the way those viruses like it.

Text.SourceString: Here we go. It’s Winter. I need to make sure I stay healthy all season.
Text.LocalizedString: Here we go. It’s Winter. I need to make sure I stay healthy all season.

Text.SourceString: Finally, the perfect weather for curry. Now <Italic>this</> is what Winter is all about.//It's like the ultimate comfort food season.
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, the perfect weather for curry. Now <Italic>this</> is what Winter is all about.//It's like the ultimate comfort food season.

Text.SourceString: I heard about Pufferfish Corp moving in…//<portrait=annoyed>It’s too bad, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I heard about Pufferfish Corp moving in…//<portrait=annoyed>It’s too bad, huh?

Text.SourceString: The islanders aren’t too happy about it either.
Text.LocalizedString: The islanders aren’t too happy about it either.

Text.SourceString: The other day, I was at the store looking for some kale for my midday snack, but guess what? <NPCName>Sam</> didn't have any. Bummer!
Text.LocalizedString: The other day, I was at the store looking for some kale for my midday snack, but guess what? <NPCName>Sam</> didn't have any. Bummer!

Text.SourceString: I guess it's not kale season anymore. Time to find another leafy green to munch on.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess it's not kale season anymore. Time to find another leafy green to munch on.

Text.SourceString: Speaking of seasonal stuff, you can get tulips, wasabi, and celery this time of year.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm… What else?
Text.LocalizedString: Speaking of seasonal stuff, you can get tulips, wasabi, and celery this time of year.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm… What else?

Text.SourceString: Wait, scratch that on the celery.//I don't think it's celery season just yet. My bad.
Text.LocalizedString: Wait, scratch that on the celery.//I don't think it's celery season just yet. My bad.

Text.SourceString: Spring just arrived, and poor <NPCName>Charles</> can't stop sneezing his nose off.//<portrait=annoyed>It's a bit worrisome, you know? I hope he finds some relief soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring just arrived, and poor <NPCName>Charles</> can't stop sneezing his nose off.//<portrait=annoyed>It's a bit worrisome, you know? I hope he finds some relief soon.

Text.SourceString: I took a walk by the lake the other day and saw so many colorful flowers.//What a season!
Text.LocalizedString: I took a walk by the lake the other day and saw so many colorful flowers.//What a season!

Text.SourceString: There are so many coconuts at the beach right now. It's like a coconut paradise out there.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many coconuts at the beach right now. It's like a coconut paradise out there.

Text.SourceString: We’re cleaning up the beach soon.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re cleaning up the beach soon.

Text.SourceString: Good thing the beach cleanup starts at 11 am.//<portrait=happy>It gives me a bit of time in the morning to stop by the clinic and pick up some stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing the beach cleanup starts at 11 am.//<portrait=happy>It gives me a bit of time in the morning to stop by the clinic and pick up some stuff.

Text.SourceString: If you're into mushrooms, there are some black trumpets and matsutakes sprouting near the mayor's house.
Text.LocalizedString: If you're into mushrooms, there are some black trumpets and matsutakes sprouting near the mayor's house.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda</> told me all about it. She's quite the foraging expert
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> told me all about it. She's quite the foraging expert

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out of hiding when she’s home.//<portrait=happy>Cute little thing.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Millie</> has a lizard that only comes out of hiding when she’s home.//<portrait=happy>Cute little thing.

Text.SourceString: She named the lizard Tin. What a fun name…
Text.LocalizedString: She named the lizard Tin. What a fun name…

Text.SourceString: I didn’t get to sleep until 3 am, and now I’m absolutely drained.//<portrait=concerned>Humph. I need to stop doing this to myself.

Text.SourceString: Oh great! Another fake medical report with a “unicorn finger problem for Yoorie.”//<NPCName>Charles</> must be bored again.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh great! Another fake medical report with a “unicorn finger problem for Yoorie.”//<NPCName>Charles</> must be bored again.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Betty</>'s one of my easy patients. I enjoy working with her.//<portrait=annoyed>But trust me, there are plenty of folks around here who make it onto my "hard patients" list.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Betty</>'s one of my easy patients. I enjoy working with her.//<portrait=annoyed>But trust me, there are plenty of folks around here who make it onto my "hard patients" list.

Text.SourceString: Can't spill the beans, though. My lips are sealed.
Text.LocalizedString: Can't spill the beans, though. My lips are sealed.

Text.SourceString: I used to be a real nomad, always traveling from one place to another.//But you know what? I don't miss it. I kinda like the stability of staying in one spot for a change.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to be a real nomad, always traveling from one place to another.//But you know what? I don't miss it. I kinda like the stability of staying in one spot for a change.

Text.SourceString: Who knew boring could be so much fun?
Text.LocalizedString: Who knew boring could be so much fun?

Text.SourceString: Just finished submitting my billing for the week.
Text.LocalizedString: Just finished submitting my billing for the week.

Text.SourceString: Feels good to get that paperwork done, even if it's not the most exciting task.
Text.LocalizedString: Feels good to get that paperwork done, even if it's not the most exciting task.

Text.SourceString: I'm here to pick up some new reading material. Already finished everything I had.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm here to pick up some new reading material. Already finished everything I had.

Text.SourceString: Weird smell, you say? Umm… No. I can’t smell anything.//But once, I lived for two years in an abandoned school right next to a dumpster.
Text.LocalizedString: Weird smell, you say? Umm… No. I can’t smell anything.//But once, I lived for two years in an abandoned school right next to a dumpster.

Text.SourceString: Maybe that messed up my sense of smell. On the bright side, the rent was free!
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe that messed up my sense of smell. On the bright side, the rent was free!

Text.SourceString: After years of hopping around, I felt the need to settle somewhere and build meaningful relationships.//That's why I ended up here on Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: After years of hopping around, I felt the need to settle somewhere and build meaningful relationships.//That's why I ended up here on Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I envy <NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</>. They seem to have such a full life.//<portrait=normal>I see them at the tavern dancing sometimes…just enjoying life together, you know?//<portrait=sad>I want that.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I envy <NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</>. They seem to have such a full life.//<portrait=normal>I see them at the tavern dancing sometimes…just enjoying life together, you know?//<portrait=sad>I want that.

Text.SourceString: Being alone is fine most of the time, but on days like today, I wouldn't mind having a partner, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Being alone is fine most of the time, but on days like today, I wouldn't mind having a partner, you know?

Text.SourceString: As soon as Summer hits, I’m wearing my bikini all the time.//<portrait=happy>I’m throwing myself at the beach every single day. Can’t wait!
Text.LocalizedString: As soon as Summer hits, I’m wearing my bikini all the time.//<portrait=happy>I’m throwing myself at the beach every single day. Can’t wait!

Text.SourceString: I got this jacket back when I was in Tangi working with the Universal Doctors.//Feel it! Good quality, right? It was really cheap too.
Text.LocalizedString: I got this jacket back when I was in Tangi working with the Universal Doctors.//Feel it! Good quality, right? It was really cheap too.

Text.SourceString: The jacket is really warm. You’d be surprised!
Text.LocalizedString: The jacket is really warm. You’d be surprised!

Text.SourceString: Spring here isn’t cold. No need to wear a thick jacket anymore.//<portrait=happy>I can move faster now!
Text.LocalizedString: Spring here isn’t cold. No need to wear a thick jacket anymore.//<portrait=happy>I can move faster now!

Text.SourceString: Normally, Spring is when I'd go to medical conferences.//But these days, I prefer attending them online. Can't beat the convenience.
Text.LocalizedString: Normally, Spring is when I'd go to medical conferences.//But these days, I prefer attending them online. Can't beat the convenience.

Text.SourceString: The conferences have free activities like scuba diving, tours, wine tastings… Yeah, It was fun.//Well, the ones I used to go to anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: The conferences have free activities like scuba diving, tours, wine tastings… Yeah, It was fun.//Well, the ones I used to go to anyway.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what kind of medical conferences they've got lined up for this upcoming Spring. Might be worth checking out!
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what kind of medical conferences they've got lined up for this upcoming Spring. Might be worth checking out!
